<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

										DAILY SLEEP DIARY
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 02-23-2016
last updated:  02-21-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-21-2022 Millisecond Software
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
This script implements a computerized version of a Daily Sleep Diary.

Kevin Morgan, Beverley David, Claire Gascoigne (2007). Clinical Sleep Research Unit Loughborough University UK.
http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/insomnia/documents/sleepdiary.pdf

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Each morning, participants answer 8 questions about their sleep.										  

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 1.5 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'dailysleepdiary.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	 with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)
								
(2) Summary data file: 'dailysleepdiary_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version: 						Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

textbox.id.response:							assigned id (if different than subjectId)
textbox.dayCount.response:						entered day count 
textbox.q1_bedtime.response-
radiobuttons.q8_sleepQualityRating.response: 	responses to question 1-8
 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
can be edited under Editable Parameters

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:				Instructions for Diary
/dateFormat:					"DMY" (day/month/year), "MDY" (month/day/year, default), "YMD" (year/month/day)

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Complete the diary each morning (“Day 1” will be your first morning). Don’t worry too much about giving exact answers; an estimate will do.
"
/dateFormat = "MDY"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,
textbox.id.response, textbox.dayCount.response, 
textbox.q1_bedtime.response, textbox.q2_fallAsleep.response, textbox.q3_nrWakeUp.response,
textbox.q4_awake.response, textbox.q5_wakeUp.response, textbox.q6_getUp.response,
textbox.q7_timeInBed.response, radiobuttons.q8_sleepQualityRating.response)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/todayDate1:			stores the local date in format mmddyy
/todayDate:				stores the local date in format mm/dd/yy			

<values>
/todayDate1 = script.startDate
/todayDate = ""
</values>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/todayDate:			converts the script.startDate into the specified format

2020-01-03



<expressions>
/todayDate = {
		values.todayDate = "";
		values.todayDate1 = script.startDate;
		if (parameters.dateFormat == "MDY") {
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 5, 2));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 8, 2));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 0, 4));	
			values.todayDate;
		} else if (parameters.dateFormat == "DMY") {
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 8, 2));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 5, 2));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 0, 4));	
			values.todayDate;
		} else {
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 0, 4));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 5, 2));
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, "/");
			values.todayDate = concat(values.todayDate, subString(values.todayDate1, 8, 2));
			values.todayDate;
		}
}	
</expressions>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<caption todayDate>
/ caption = "

Today's Date is: <%expressions.todayDate%>"
/ txcolor = blue
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</caption>

<textbox dayCount>
/ caption = "Day (Day1 will be your first morning):"
/ required = true
/ mask = integer
/ textboxsize = (5%, 2.5%)
</textbox>

<textbox id>
/ caption = "Your Identification Number:"
/ required = true
/ multiline = true
/ maxchars = 100
/ textboxsize = (50%, 5%)
</textbox>

<textbox q1_bedtime>
/ caption = "1. At what time did you go to bed last night?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q2_fallAsleep>
/ caption = "2. After settling down, how long did it take you to fall asleep?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q3_nrWakeUp>
/ caption = "3. After falling asleep, about how many times did you wake up in the night?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q4_awake>
/ caption = "4. After falling asleep, for how long were you awake during the night in total?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q5_wakeUp>
/ caption = "5. At what time did you finally wake up?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q6_getUp>
/ caption = "6. At what time did you get up?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<textbox q7_timeInBed>
/ caption = "7. How long did you spend in bed last night (from first getting in, to finally getting up)?"
/ required = true
</textbox>

<radiobuttons q8_sleepQualityRating>
/ caption = "8. How would you rate the quality of your sleep last night? "
/ options = ("1~nVery Poor", "2~n     ", "3~n     ", "4~n     ", "5~nVery Good")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation= horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage SD1>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = todayDate, daycount, id]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SD2>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = todayDate, q1_bedtime, q2_fallAsleep, q3_nrWakeUp]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SD3>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = todayDate, q4_awake, q5_wakeUp, q6_getUp]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SD4>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = todayDate, q7_timeInBed, q8_sleepQualityRating]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey DailySleepDiary>
/pages = [
	1 = SD1; 
	2 = SD2; 
	3 = SD3;
	4 = SD4;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/showpagenumbers = false
/showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

*******************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
*******************************************************************************************************************